Where to place your toggle?
1. Toggles at the edge
need per-request context (Experiment Toggles, Permissioning Toggles)?
- place Toggle Points in the edge services of your system
- the publicly exposed web apps that present functionality to end users.
This is where requests first enter your domain,
thus where your Toggle Router has the most context available
to make toggling decisions based on the user and their request.
2. Toggles in the core
There are other types of lower-level toggle which must be placed deeper
- usually technical in nature
- control how some functionality is implemented internally
ex. Release Toggle which controls whether to use a new piece of caching infrastructure
in front of a third-party API or just route requests directly to that API.
